  26,2,These are the verses of the clear Book
  26,3,Perhaps you ňĻO Prophetňļ will grieve yourself to death over their disbelief
  26,4,"If We willed, We could send down upon them a ňĻcompellingňļ sign from the heavens, leaving their necks bent in ňĻutterňļ submission to it"
  26,5,"Whatever new reminder comes to them from the Most Compassionate, they always turn away from it"
  26,6,"They have certainly denied ňĻthe truthňļ, so they will soon face the consequences of their ridicule"
  26,7,"Have they failed to look at the earth, ňĻto seeňļ how many types of fine plants We have caused to grow in it"
  26,8,Surely in this is a sign. Yet most of them would not believe
  26,9,"And your Lord is certainly the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  26,10,"ňĻRememberňļ when your Lord called out to Moses, ‚ÄúGo to the wrongdoing people‚ÄĒ"
  26,11,the people of Pharaoh. Will they not fear ňĻGodňļ?‚ÄĚ
  26,12,"He replied, ‚ÄúMy Lord! I fear that they will reject me"
  26,13,And ňĻsoňļ my heart will be broken and my tongue will be tied. So send Aaron along ňĻas a messengerňļ
  26,14,"Also, they have a charge against me,¬†so I fear they may kill me.‚ÄĚ"
  26,15,"God responded, ‚ÄúCertainly not! So go, both of you, with Our signs. We will be with you, listening"
  26,16,"Go to Pharaoh and say, ‚ÄėWe are messengers from the Lord of all worlds"
  26,17,"ňĻcommanded to say:ňļ ‚ÄėLet the Children of Israel go with us.‚Äô‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  26,18,"Pharaoh protested, ‚ÄúDid we not raise you among us as a child, and you stayed several years of your life in our care"
  26,19,"Then you did what you did,¬†being ňĻutterlyňļ ungrateful!‚ÄĚ"
  26,20,"Moses replied, ‚ÄúI did it then, lacking guidance"
  26,21,So I fled from you when I feared you. Then my Lord granted me wisdom and made me one of the messengers
  26,22,"How can that be a ‚Äėfavour,‚Äô of which you remind me, when ňĻit was only becauseňļ you ňĻhaveňļ enslaved the Children of Israel?‚ÄĚ"
  26,23,"Pharaoh asked, ‚ÄúAnd what is ‚Äėthe Lord of all worlds‚Äô?‚ÄĚ"
  26,24,"Moses replied, ‚ÄúňĻHe isňļ the Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in between, if only you had sure faith.‚ÄĚ"
  26,25,"Pharaoh said to those around him, ‚ÄúDid you hear ňĻwhat he saidňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  26,26,"Moses added, ‚ÄúňĻHe isňļ your Lord and the Lord of your forefathers.‚ÄĚ"
  26,27,"Pharaoh said ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúYour messenger, who has been sent to you, must be insane.‚ÄĚ"
  26,28,"Moses responded: ‚ÄúňĻHe isňļ the Lord of the east and west, and everything in between, if only you had any sense.‚ÄĚ"
  26,29,"Pharaoh threatened, ‚ÄúIf you take any other god besides me, I will certainly have you imprisoned.‚ÄĚ"
  26,30,"Moses responded, ‚ÄúEven if I bring you a clear proof?‚ÄĚ"
  26,31,"Pharaoh demanded, ‚ÄúBring it then, if what you say is true.‚ÄĚ"
  26,32,So he threw down his staff and‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒit became a real snake
  26,33,Then he drew his hand ňĻout of his collarňļ and it was ňĻshiningňļ white for all to see
  26,34,"Pharaoh said to the chiefs around him, ‚ÄúHe is indeed a skilled magician"
  26,35,who seeks to drive you from your land by his magic. So what do you propose?‚ÄĚ
  26,36,"They replied, ‚ÄúLet him and his brother wait and dispatch mobilizers to all cities"
  26,37,to bring you every skilled magician.‚ÄĚ
  26,38,So the magicians were assembled at the set time on the appointed day
  26,39,"And the people were asked, ‚ÄúWill you join the gathering"
  26,40,so that we may follow the magicians if they prevail?‚ÄĚ
  26,41,"When the magicians came, they asked Pharaoh, ‚ÄúShall we have a ňĻsuitableňļ reward if we prevail?‚ÄĚ"
  26,42,"He replied, ‚ÄúYes, and you will then certainly be among those closest to me.‚ÄĚ"
  26,43,"Moses said to them, ‚ÄúCast whatever you wish to cast.‚ÄĚ"
  26,44,"So they cast down their ropes and staffs, saying, ‚ÄúBy Pharaoh‚Äôs might, it is we who will surely prevail.‚ÄĚ"
  26,45,"Then Moses threw down his staff, and‚ÄĒbehold!‚ÄĒit devoured the objects of their illusion"
  26,46,"So the magicians fell down, prostrating"
  26,47,"They declared, ‚ÄúWe ňĻnowňļ believe in the Lord of all worlds‚ÄĒ"
  26,48,the Lord of Moses and Aaron.‚ÄĚ
  26,49,"Pharaoh threatened, ‚ÄúHow dare you believe in him before I give you permission? He must be your master who taught you magic, but soon you will see. I will certainly cut off your hands and feet on opposite sides, then crucify you all.‚ÄĚ"
  26,50,"They responded, ‚ÄúňĻThat would beňļ no harm! Surely to our Lord we will ňĻallňļ return"
  26,51,"We really hope that our Lord will forgive our sins, as we are the first to believe.‚ÄĚ"